1.1 Philadelphia
1.2 New Hampshire


2 Abolitionist minister

2.1 New York and the Abolitionist Movement
2.2 Return to Philadelphia
2.3 Move to the South


3 Reconstruction politician

3.1 1868 Constitutional Convention and rise to Secretary of State
3.2 Superintendent of Public Instruction


4 Death
5 Legacy and impact
